The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks and convolutional neural networks for machine learning tasks, which are commonly studied in the computer science sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also presents a method for reducing numerical precision of weights and activations, which falls under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the computational efficiency of the proposed method, which is related to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
